<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts(Clutter.Container, gfloat, gfloat, gfloat)
@returns(none)
def do_get_preferred_width(self, container, for_height, min_width_p, nat_width_p):
</code></synopsis>
<p>Computes the minimum and natural widths of the @container according
to @manager.</p><p>See also clutter_actor_get_preferred_width()</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>container :</p></td>
<td><p>the <link xref="Clutter.Container">Clutter.Container</link> using @manager</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>for_height :</p></td>
<td><p>the height for which the width should be computed, or -1</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>min_width_p :</p></td>
<td><p>return location for the minimum width of the layout, or None</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td><p>nat_width_p :</p></td>
<td><p>return location for the natural width of the layout, or None</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
<p>Since 1.2</p>
